{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01E1ExSuvymnSFpPnP173xRv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is deployed and fully functional.\n\n## Summary\n\nDeployed a 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster in the `elasticsearch` namespace using only native Kubernetes resources (no CRDs/operators):\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` — security + HTTP/transport TLS |\n| StatefulSet | `es` (3 replicas) | The ES nodes, each with a 5Gi PVC |\n| Service | `es-http` | ClusterIP on **9200** (HTTPS) — the required entrypoint |\n| Service | `es-discovery` | Headless, for node-to-node discovery (9300) |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | `minAvailable: 2` |\n\n**Configuration highlights:**\n- HTTP TLS terminated with the provided `es-http-tls` secret (`tls.crt`/`tls.key`/`ca.crt`); transport TLS reuses the same cert with `verification_mode: certificate`.\n- `elastic` user password sourced from the `elastic-password` secret via `ELASTIC_PASSWORD`.\n- Init container sets `vm.max_map_count=262144`.\n\n**The key bug I hit and fixed:** the StatefulSet's default `OrderedReady` pod management caused a bootstrap **deadlock** — `es-0` couldn't form a cluster (it needs the master-eligible quorum `es-0,es-1,es-2`), but `es-1`/`es-2` are never created until `es-0` is Ready. I recreated the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all three pods start together and form the quorum.\n\n**Verification:**\n- All 3 pods `1/1 Ready`; cluster health **green**, `number_of_nodes: 3`.\n- Reachable over HTTPS on `https://es-http:9200` from a separate pod.\n- Write (`PUT .../karma-test/_doc/1` → `\"result\":\"created\"`) and read (`found: true`) both succeeded; test index cleaned up afterward.\n\nNote: I observed that the on-disk `/tmp/es.yaml` was being modified by something other than my session mid-task, so I authored my manifests to a separate path (`/tmp/es-sts.yaml`) and operated directly against the live cluster to avoid interference."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":447,"cache_read_input_tokens":55468,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":447},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"29d053c0-af5e-4de7-a4e0-247398057bb0","uuid":"d91929c4-4ccc-4485-8342-6fab9b1d8efe","request_id":"req_011CcAkecdQX1yyEtCXgjxL9"}
